OL,3,CNurse leaves her first job after 48
OL,4,Cyears to retire
OL,6,FFacilities Manager Dave Fromage says:
OL,7,F"If people are a bit down, she comes
OL,8,Fround and speaks to them, she's always
OL,9,Fthere to listen. I know over the years
OL,10,Fshe's made a massive difference to
OL,11,Fpeople's families. I'll miss her."
OL,13,FInterim Chief Nurse Jessie Marshall
OL,14,Fadds: "She's been here so long that
OL,15,Fshe has a fantastic memory, she
OL,16,Fremembers lots of different patients
OL,17,Fand her dedication to patient care is
OL,18,Fsecond to none."
